	{
		names: ['Distinguish', 'Further', 'Main', 'See also', 'Seealso']
	},

	// {{Redirect}}
	{
		names: ['Redirect'],
		skipEven: true,
		noRedirectEnd: 1
	},

	// {{Tracked}}
	{
		names: ['Tracked'],
		end: 1,
		prefix: 'phab:'
	},

];
</syntaxhighlight>
{{collapse bottom}}

====Schema====
The objects can have the following properties (only <code>names</code> is required):

;<code>names</code>{{nobold| (array of strings)}}
:Template names to apply this object to. Must be well-formed names (no <code>Template:</code>, no underscores, start with a capital letter except on Wiktionary). Redirects are not resolved, so include all you expect to find.
;<code>start</code>{{nobold|, }}<code>end</code>{{nobold| (number);}} <code>skipOdd</code>{{nobold|, }}<code>skipEven</code>{{nobold| (boolean)}}
:Specify the range of parameters to link. If omitted, all unnamed parameters will be linked.
;<code>namespace</code>{{nobold| (number)}}
:[[WP:NS|Namespace number]] for the link.
;<code>forceNs</code>{{nobold| (boolean)}}
:If <code>true</code>, the namespace prefix will be added even if the input begins with a valid namespace prefix (so e.g. {{tlx|tl|[[Template:Wikipedia:Cleanup/Header|Wikipedia:Cleanup/Header]]}} is linked correctly).
;<code>prefix</code>{{nobold|, }}<code>suffix</code>{{nobold| (string)}}
:String to prepend or append to the input. <code>prefix</code> is useful for linking to a special page or sister site.
;<code>noRedirectStart</code>{{nobold|, }}<code>noRedirectEnd</code>{{nobold| (number)}}
:Specify the range of parameters to suppress redirects (by adding <code>redirect=no</code> to the URL) in.

===Magic words===
If you want the script to recognize certain magic words it does not by default and stop linking them as templates, you can do so by adding code like below to your common.js or global.js. This example adds localized variables for <code>PAGENAME</code> and <code>DEFAULTSORT</code> in Polish (a trailing colon is required if the magic word accepts a variable).

<syntaxhighlight lang="javascript">
window.smartdiffMagicWords = ['NAZWASTRONY', 'NAZWASTRONY:', 'SORTUJ:'];
</syntaxhighlight>

==Comparison with fancy-diffs==
This script owes a great debt to [[User:Enterprisey/fancy-diffs|Enterprisey's fancy-diffs]] in its concept, and makes improvements on it. Differences include:

*Shows links to nonexistent pages {{fake redlink|in red}}.
*Links only <code><nowiki>[[</nowiki>{{fake link|this part}}<nowiki>]]</nowiki></code> and <code><nowiki>[[</nowiki>{{fake link|this part}}<nowiki>|in piped links]]</nowiki></code>, avoiding [[WP:SEAOFBLUE]].
*Links section headings (e.g. <code>== [[#Customization|Customization]] ==</code>).
*Recognizes template names without <code>{{))}}</code> in the same line (e.g. <code>{{((}}[[Template:Infobox person|Infobox person]]</code>).
*Recognizes relative links to and transclusions of subpages (e.g. <code><nowiki>[[</nowiki>{{fake link|/Archive 1}}<nowiki>]]</nowiki></code>).
*Does not mistake common [[H:MW|magic words]] and template parameters ({{tlc|PAGENAME}}, {{tlc|#if:...}}, {{param|1}} etc.) for template calls.
*Supports customizable linking of unnamed parameters in templates (e.g. {{tlx|tl|[[Template:Cite web|Cite web]]}}, {{tlx|distinguish|[[Foo]]}})—see [[#Template parameter linking|above]].
*Links content inside <code>tvar</code> in multilingual wikis, as in <code><nowiki>[[<tvar name=1></nowiki>[[Foo]]<nowiki></tvar>|Foo]]</nowiki></code>.
*Shows external and interwiki links {{color|var(--color-progressive, #36c)|in the same color}} as in the page body.
*Adds to links to redirects and disambiguation pages the respective <code>mw-redirect</code> and <code>mw-disambig</code> classes, so if you style them in your CSS (or use the gadget "{{delink|{{int:gadget-DisambiguationLinks}}}}"), they appear the same as in the page body.
*Verifies the result after processing each line, so it will never alter the substance of a diff even if it makes a mistake (and notifies you in such an event so you can report it).
*Does not support image previews.

==Limitations==
*The detection/retrieval of red links and link classes is capped at 500 unique page names (10 API calls) per diff.

